LOCUS       PCymRC                    90 bp    DNA     linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  CymR-repressible synthetic promoter: a sigma70 core (-35/-10)
            flanked by two cumate operators (CuO); CymR binding represses
            transcription and the inducer p-cumate relieves it.
